text: Tried the noodle stall in this corner shop. Not big for a coffee shop. The fish balls noodle was acceptable though the fish balls can be better with plain ones instead those mixed with veg and chili. Like the soup though.
Recently repainted. Great beer in the evenings. The È∫ªËæ£È¶ôÈîÖ is üëç. Minced pork noodle is wonderful. The chicken rice is of a very high quality. Must try the curry chicken noodles too.

There is this newly open Malay stall call Warong Belado. Tried it today. Food very nice. The Sotong Hitam is power. Mee Rebus also very flavourful. The sambal Belado is damn power. Will try the rest of the dish someday soon.

I like Lam's Noodles here. They sell bah chor mee. The coffeeshop is not crowded but gotta wait 10 min for the noodles. My wife likes the Fei Fei yong tau hoo. The teh is usually diluted. The coffeeis ok.

Coffeeshop. But seems like a lot of closed stalls.
Nothing much to eat after 3pm.
